gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Knicks 119, Warriors 112
gameRecap.excerpt: The Knicks win their fourth straight game as they defeat the Warriors, 119-112. Jalen Brunson led all scorers with 34 points, along with five rebounds and seven assists for the Knicks, his third straight game with 30+ points, while Miles McBride added a career-high 29 points and six 3PM in the victory. Josh Hart (10 points, 11 rebounds, 11 assists) recorded his 5th triple-double of the season, and 5th of his career for the Knicks, doing so by playing in all 48 minutes. Stephen Curry tallied 27 points, five rebounds and five assists for the Warriors in the losing effort. The Knicks improve to 41-27 on the season, while the Warriors fall to 35-32.
